Agent_1_Report estimates $45-75 monthly runtime costs and 28-36 hours total effort, while Agent_2_Report estimates $1.60 per run and 11.0 hours total effort. Both analyze the same populate_dimensions stored procedure but use different cost models and complexity assessments. Semantic similarity is high (85/100) as both address migration planning, but structural approaches differ substantially (70/100). Both reports are syntactically correct (100/100 each).

Both outputs address Synapse to Fabric migration cost estimation and effort planning for the same stored procedure. Agent_1_Report assumes complexity score 35/100 and nightly execution frequency, while Agent_2_Report focuses on single execution scenarios. Both correctly identify MERGE operations as primary conversion challenge and include similar business rule validation requirements.

Both reports follow similar high-level structure with Cost Estimation, Code Fixing sections, and API costs. However, significant structural differences exist: Agent_1_Report uses 4-tier cost breakdown (Fabric Compute, Storage, Network, Performance Optimizations) while Agent_2_Report uses simpler 3-component model (Complexity, Data Volume, Execution Time).
